## Summary

In `buildContributorOutcomeHistory` (`src/signals/engine.ts`), every per-repo outcome field falls back to a **cache-derived** value when the official Gittensor snapshot has no entry for the repo — *except* the two issue-discovery fields, which fall back to a literal `0`:

```ts
// src/signals/engine.ts:1452-1461
const cachedPrs = args.pullRequests.filter((pr) => sameRepo(pr.repoFullName, repoFullName) && sameLogin(pr.authorLogin, args.login));
const cachedIssues = args.issues.filter((issue) => sameRepo(issue.repoFullName, repoFullName) && sameLogin(issue.authorLogin, args.login));
const pullRequests      = official?.pullRequests      ?? Math.max(cachedPrs.length, cachedStat?.pullRequests ?? 0);
const mergedPullRequests= official?.mergedPullRequests?? Math.max(cachedPrs.filter((pr) => pr.mergedAt || pr.state === "merged").length, cachedStat?.mergedPullRequests ?? 0);
const openPullRequests  = official?.openPullRequests  ?? Math.max(...);
const closedPullRequests= official?.closedPullRequests?? Math.max(...);
const openIssues        = official?.openIssues        ?? cachedIssues.filter((issue) => issue.state === "open").length;
const closedIssues      = official?.closedIssues      ?? cachedIssues.filter((issue) => issue.state !== "open").length;
const solvedIssues      = official?.solvedIssues      ?? 0;   // <- no cache fallback
const validSolvedIssues = official?.validSolvedIssues ?? 0;   // <- no cache fallback
```

So for any contributor not present in the official Gittensor API (a cache-only contributor — i.e. most new/unranked contributors), `solvedIssues` and `validSolvedIssues` are **always 0**, even when their cached issues were solved by their own merged PRs.

This is purely a dropped value, not a missing capability: the engine already classifies issue-discovery outcomes from cache. `classifyIssueDiscoveryLifecycle` derives `valid_solved` / `solved` states from exactly the data in scope here (cached issues + PRs + lane):

```ts
// src/signals/engine.ts:2764-2776 (classifyIssueDiscoveryLifecycle)
const state = duplicate ? "duplicate" : invalid ? "invalid"
  : solvedByPullRequests.length > 0
    ? (lane.lane === "issue_discovery" || lane.lane === "split" ? "valid_solved" : "solved")
    : issue.state !== "open" ? "closed_not_solved" : stale ? "stale" : "open";
```

and `buildIssueDiscoveryLifecycleReport` (`engine.ts:2675`) already aggregates `valid_solved` counts from cache. None of that is wired into `buildContributorOutcomeHistory`.

